messages.messageBody:
Awesome!
Josh just tweaked his excel spreadsheet that keeps up with his
earnings, because today he discovered at Nintendo.com that there is a
definite date and price for the new Nintendo Wii (and anyone who was
cornered by him at the conference should know details about it, it is
def his passion right now) So he has up to $230 saved, and today
realized that he did NOT figure in tax, plus an additional
controller, because who wants to play by themselves? However, he has
an additional three weeks in which to make said money. He also
realized that mom wanted his old one, and was willing to pay cash to
buy it for the girls to have, and also that he could finagle an
additional 10% out of me to guarantee not to sell it at game xchange.
Smart, huh? I love video games!
Melissa
Mom to Josh (11), Breanna (9), Emily (7), Rachel (6), Sam (5), Dan
(3), and Avari Rose

share our lives at
http://360.yahoo.com/multimomma
